As the update was being issued, a strong supercell evolved near the Louisiana-Mississippi border. By 7:57&nbsp;pm. CDT, a strong Weather radar#Velocity|velocity couplet formed at the base of the supercell, which then produced what would become this long-tracked violent EF4 tornado, and at 8:04&nbsp;pm, as the storm approached the town of Rolling Fork, a tornado emergency was placed. Afterwards, the tornado struck Rolling Fork, Mississippi|Rolling Fork, Midnight, Mississippi|Midnight, and Silver City, Mississippi|Silver City, inflicting catastrophic damage and causing over a dozen fatalities. While the violent EF4 tornado was on the ground, Harry Weinman, a forecaster at the SPC, issued a special meso-gamma mesoscale discussion for the tornado. The discussion concluded by noting that the downstream atmospheric environment would allow the storm producing the violent EF4 tornado to persist for 30 to 60 minutes.
